Process called "is_reserved_keyword" takes word as Integer returns Integer:
    Note:
    Table-free single-word keyword check (canonical Keywords export).

    Determines whether a bare identifier string is one of Runa's reserved
    keywords without requiring a pre-built KeywordTable. This is the form
    consumed by sibling modules (import_resolver, encasing_handler) that
    need a stateless yes/no answer during alias and identifier validation.

    Parameters:
      word - Pointer to a NUL-terminated identifier string (no spaces)

    Returns:
      1 if the word is a reserved Runa keyword
      0 otherwise (including a null pointer)

    Implementation:
    Direct case-sensitive comparison against the complete single-word
    keyword set. The set is kept byte-identical to the keywords registered
    in create_keyword_table so the two recognition paths never diverge.
    :End Note

    If word is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Compare against each reserved keyword. string_compare returns 1 on
    Note: an exact case-sensitive match, matching the convention used throughout
